---
title: "Buy & Sell St. Pete Like a Local | Everlane Realty"
description: "Search every home for sale in St. Petersburg & Tampa Bay, get an honest broker-prepared home valuation, and book a consult — with Serge Osaulenko at Everlane Realty."
jsonld: ["real-estate-agent"]
---
{#- HOME — THE LOCKED 10-SECTION GRAMMAR (design lock 2026-07-07;
    rationale.md §2 — order is BOUND):
      1 mast (base.njk) · 2 hero + 3 verify byline (AMENDED per the operator's
      r2 verdict) · 4 doorways · 5 live-data band · 6 listings · 7 neighborhoods
      · 8 knowledge base · 9 proof block · 10 booking band + footer (base.njk).
    data-sec attributes are the check-suite's grammar-order invariant.

    BUILD-COUPLINGS honored here:
    - NL search doorway = PLAIN LINK into /search/ (rationale §6: the smart box
      ships only WITH wave 3; a dead smart box would be worse than none).
      Wave 3 mounts the NL affordance inside the Buying door below.
    - "listings synced" line renders ONLY from feed.listingsSyncedAgo (real
      feed-watcher value; null at wave 1 → the line does not exist in HTML).
    - IDX saved-search signup widget (wave-1 staged remainder, ask #1) mounts
      in the listings section — slot comment below. The map widget lives on
      /search/ per the locked grammar; it no longer embeds on home. -#}

<div class="hero-ed" data-sec="hero">
  <div class="hero-ed__words">
    <p class="kicker">A licensed Florida brokerage &middot; St. Petersburg &amp; Tampa Bay</p>
    <h1 class="display">Buy &amp; sell St.&nbsp;Pete like&nbsp;a&nbsp;local.</h1>
    <p class="sub">Real MLS data, honest numbers, and a broker who actually picks up the phone &mdash;
    backed by the city&rsquo;s most local guide, neighborhood by neighborhood.</p>
    <div class="ctas">
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/search/">Search homes</a>
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/valuation/">What&rsquo;s my home worth?</a>
      <a class="quiet" href="/contact/">Or book a consult &rarr;</a>
    </div>

    {#- VERIFY BYLINE — the r2 design amendment, implemented: photo = 25% of
        the block's left (specified range: 20–30%), info right, one tight
        bordered strip on paper ground, whitespace tightened. The photo stays
        small; the full proof layer stays at №5 by the same decision. -#}
    <div class="verify" data-sec="verify">
      <div class="verify__photo">
        <img src="/assets/headshot-serge.jpg" alt="Serge Osaulenko, Broker at Everlane Realty" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;display:block">
      </div>
      <div class="verify__info">
        <p class="verify__name" style="margin:0">Serge Osaulenko, Broker</p>
        <ul class="creds">
          <li>FL License #BK3384892</li>
          <li>FSU &mdash; Real Estate &amp; Finance</li>
          <li>English &amp; Русский</li>
          <li>Broker/owner since 2020 &middot; licensed since 2017</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="verify__more"><a href="/team/serge-osaulenko/">About Serge &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  {%- if images.home %}
  <div class="hero-ed__plate hero-ed__plate--img">
    <img src="{{ images.home.src }}" srcset="{{ images.home.srcset }}" sizes="(min-width: 900px) 50vw, 100vw" alt="St. Petersburg waterfront — vintage-postcard-style illustration" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1600" height="1067">
  </div>
  {%- else %}
  <div class="hero-ed__plate" role="img" aria-label="Photo placeholder — Old Northeast at dusk">
    <p class="plate-note">photo placeholder &mdash; Old Northeast, 6:48&nbsp;pm</p>
  </div>
  {%- endif %}
</div>

<section class="section" data-sec="doors">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head"><div><span class="no">№ 1 &middot; Start here</span><h2>Buying, selling, or just asking</h2></div></div>

    {#- Live homepage ask module (design-review fix 1, 2026-07-10): surfaces the
        concierge as a first-class entry — a GET form + chips that deep-link into
        /ask/?q=… (ask.js reads q and auto-sends). No network path on home; the
        experience lives on /ask. COPY GUARD: no MLS-search phrasing. -#}
    <form class="home-ask" action="/ask/" method="get" role="search" aria-label="Ask Lane, Everlane's assistant">
      <div class="home-ask__id">
        <span class="home-ask__name">Lane</span><span class="home-ask__sub">&mdash; Everlane&rsquo;s assistant</span>
      </div>
      <p class="home-ask__lead">Ask a plain-English question about buying or selling in St.&nbsp;Petersburg &mdash; grounded answers from Everlane&rsquo;s own knowledge base, with a real broker behind them.</p>
      <div class="home-ask__row">
        <label for="home-ask-input" class="sr-only">Ask Lane a question</label>
        <input id="home-ask-input" name="q" type="text" maxlength="500" autocomplete="off" placeholder="Ask about flood zones, a neighborhood, taxes, or the buying process…">
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary">Ask</button>
      </div>
      <div class="home-ask__chips">
        <span class="home-ask__try">Try</span>
        <a class="chip" href="/ask/?q=What%20does%20flood%20zone%20AE%20mean%20for%20insurance%3F">Flood zone AE &amp; insurance</a>
        <a class="chip" href="/ask/?q=Can%20I%20run%20an%20Airbnb%20in%20Gulfport%3F">Airbnb in Gulfport?</a>
        <a class="chip" href="/ask/?q=How%20does%20the%20homestead%20exemption%20work%3F">Homestead exemption</a>
      </div>
    </form>

    <div class="doors">
      <div class="door">
        <span class="d-eyebrow">Buying</span>
        <h3>Search every listing</h3>
        <p>Stellar MLS listings across St. Pete and Tampa Bay, refreshed through the day &mdash; map,
        filters, and saved-search alerts.</p>
        {#- BUILD-COUPLING (rationale §6): the plain-English "type it like you'd
            say it" search box mounts HERE only WITH the wave-3 concierge/NL
            layer. Until then the doorway is a normal link — no dead smart box. -#}
        <a class="go" href="/search/">Open the full search</a>
      </div>
      <div class="door">
        <span class="d-eyebrow">Selling</span>
        <h3>What&rsquo;s your home worth &mdash; honestly</h3>
        <p>No instant gimmick number. Tell us about the house; a broker-prepared price analysis, grounded
        in real comparable sales, comes back within 24 hours.</p>
        <a class="go" href="/valuation/">Start the valuation</a>
      </div>
      <div class="door">
        <span class="d-eyebrow">Not sure yet</span>
        <h3>Talk it through first</h3>
        <p>Fifteen minutes, no pitch, no obligation. Give me the messy version &mdash; I&rsquo;ll make it clear.</p>
        <a class="go" href="/contact/">Book a consult</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

